<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">298. McKelvey, Susan. Light & Shadows: Optical Illusions in Quilts. Lafayette, CA: C & T, 1989. 79 pp. Bibl., endnotes/footnotes, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-914881-20-5. </p><p class="annot">Information, illustrations, and projects focus on the use of color tocreate three-dimensional and transparency illusions in quilts. This book supplements McKelveyâ€™s earlier Color for Quilters. The text is clear and concise, but it is the 16 pages of color illustrations and the worksheets for color experimentation that will inspire the quiltmaker who wants to use color in new ways. </p></div>
